                    <div class="w-full md:w-3/5 md:pr-12 space-y-4">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-shadow-soft text-brand-green">Why Warehouse Floors Fail — And What It's Actually Costing Your Operation</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 space-y-4">In a distribution center or manufacturing warehouse, the concrete slab isn't just a floor — it is the operating platform for every piece of material handling equipment, every racked pallet, and every employee on foot. An unprotected or under-specified warehouse floor is not a static problem. It degrades progressively, generating dust, surface defects, trip hazards, and equipment wear that compound daily into measurable operational and financial losses. A correctly engineered <strong><u>warehouse floor epoxy system</u></strong> is not a cosmetic upgrade — it is a infrastructure protection investment.</p>
                    </div>
